Package: lorenzpartition
Title: Lorenz Partition Distribution
Version: 0.1.11
Authors@R: c(person(given="David B.",family="Dahl",role=c("aut","cre"),email="dahl@stat.byu.edu",comment=c(ORCID="0000-0002-8173-1547")),
             person(given="Richard L.",family="Warr",role=c("aut"),email="warr@stat.byu.edu",comment=c(ORCID="0000-0001-8508-3105")),
             person(given="Talmage",family="Hilton",role=c("aut"),email="hilto24@student.byu.edu"),
             person(given = "Authors of the dependency Rust crates", role = "ctb", comment = "see inst/AUTHORS file for details"))
Description: Implements the Lorenz partition distribution, a prior on set
    partitions that separates the number of clusters k, the integer partition
    (cluster sizes) given k, and the allocation of items to clusters. The
    integer partition component uses a sequential kernel construction (TiDaL or
    TaDPoLe) whose target is specified via Lorenz curve increments. Functions
    are provided to evaluate the probability mass function ('dlorenzip'), draw
    random samples ('rlorenzip'), construct Lorenz curves ('lorenz_linear',
    'lorenz_ispline'), and run diagnostic comparisons ('downsample',
    'crp_vs_lorenz'). See Dahl, Warr, and Hilton (2025+) for details.
